Since Kelly seems to be finishing up her Reform, I think I'm about
ready to post the proposal suite I've been working up.  I will note
that it is designed to work on top of any type of voting/proposal
system; it merely augments.  Anyway, here are proposals DB17-[1-5].

Proto-PROPOSAL DB17-1 (Vanyel)
Submission of Votes
Amend Rule 1036 to read as follows:

Each Player shall have a Proposal Queue.  Any time a Player sends
a Proposal to the Speaker, eir Proposal is added to eir Queue.
At the beginning of the Nomic Week, the maximum length of the
for-Vote Proposal Queue is set to the current number of Active
Players.  If at any time the total number of Proposals in all
Proposal Queues is less than this maximum length, then all Proposals
are cleared from the Player Queues and placed in the for-Vote Proposal
Queue.  If there are more Proposals than this limit, Proposals will
be placed in the for-Vote Queue only as determined elsewhere in the
Rules.  As Soon As Possible after the Proposals are placed in the
for-Vote Queue, the Speaker should assign each a Number and distribute
them to all Players for Voting.

All Proposals which are "put up for Vote" as specified elsewhere in
the Rules are placed in the for-Vote Proposal Queue iff that would
not fill the for-Vote Queue past its maximum; if it would, then those
Proposals are placed in a Priority Queue which must be emptied into
the for-Vote Queue before any other Proposals may be placed there.

Proto-PROPOSAL DB17-2 (Vanyel)
Determining Order of Votes

If the total number of Proposals in existence exceeds the maximum
number allowed in the for-Vote Proposal Queue, the Speaker shall go
through the following process to determine which Proposals to put in
the for-Vote Proposal Queue:
     1)	E shall make a list of all Players in descending order by Honour.
     2)	E shall go through the list and remove each Player without any
	Proposals in eir Proposal Queue.
     3) E shall go through the list in order, taking the first Proposal
	in the queue of each Player and adding it to the for-Vote Queue
	until the for-Vote Queue is full.
     4) If the Speaker completes the list, having taken one Proposal from
	each Player's Proposal queue, e shall return to Step 2 and repeat.
Once e has filled the for-Vote Proposal Queue, e shall follow any steps
specified elsewhere in the Rules which apply.

This Rule defers to any Rule which specifies another method of determining
which Votes to be put up for Vote.

If [Proto DB17-1] does not pass, then this Rule immediately will repeal 
itself.

PROTO-Proposal DB17-3 (Vanyel)
Proposal Retraction

The only way a Proposal may be prematurely retracted by a Player 
is if e, the Player, specifically requests such to the Speaker.
The Player may not replace a Proposal with another; if e retracts
it, e can only replace it by submitting another Proposal.  Any 
retractions shall discard a Proposal irrevocably.

The Player may also request that a Proposal authored by eim
be removed from the Proposals up for Vote by stating such to the Public 
Forum.  In such a case, any points which would be received as a direct
result of that Proposal shall be distributed; then, that Proposal
will be irrevocably retracted.  Any points which have been spent on
Vototron contributions are returned, and any Votes cast for that
Proposal shall be disregarded.

PROTO-Proposal DB17-4 (Vanyel)
Proposal Clumping

A Player may decide to Clump a group of Proposals which were adjacently
Proposed (i.e. with no other Proposals between or among them).  E must
pay a fee for this; 1 point per Proposal for a Clump of less than 7
Proposals, or 3 points per Proposal for Clumps of at least 7.  No
Clumps may be of more than 15 Proposals.

If for some reason not all Proposals in existence shall be Voted
on, then if the Speaker selects any one Proposal of the Clump to
be put up for Vote, all of the Proposals of the Clump are put up
for Vote  If it is the case that this would put too many Proposals
up for Vote, then none of the Proposals in the Clump are put up for
Vote.

Proposals in a Clump are voted on separately, and all point changes
involving them are dealt with separately, however all of the
Proposals in a Clump must Pass, or else none take effect.  In other
words, if a single Proposal in a Clump Fails, then all shall Fail.
This does not affect point changes such as F-A bonuses in any way.

Proto-PROPOSAL DB17-5 (Vanyel)
Repeal 1065

Rule 1065 shall be Repealed.  [Proposal fees for >2 props.]
***END PROTO SUITE

proposal history:
first proto 7 Oct 12:35 PM CDT
second proto 14 Oct 5:43 PM CDT
third proto (suite) 8 Nov 7:00 PM CST

The previous versions of these protoes were all in a single proto;
I separated them on the request of (I believe) Kelly.  I have modified
a couple details to compensate for changes since mid-October, and I've
made them as independent of each other as possible, so in the final
Suite you needn't worry about voting for one and not another; this 
should be alright.  The only Proto which depends on another is DB17-2;
it requires DB17-1.  Let me stress, in the wake of CFJ 715, that the
"Player Proposal Queues" and stuff doesn't *have* to be anything more
than a mental construct in the mind of the Speaker...

Comments, questions?

Vanyel

